This question assumes a generational cohort refers to a group of people born within a specific time period; 
A shopping channel is a platform or method through which transactions are made, such as online or in-store; 
Gender refers to the respondents' biological or identified gender.

A generational cohort refers to a group of people born within a specific time period, which may influence their spending habits and preferences; 
Shopping channels can include online marketplaces, brick-and-mortar stores, or other platforms where transactions occur;
Total amount spent can be used to analyze consumer behavior and preferences among different cohorts and channels.

sql:
SELECT 
  (SELECT AVG(amount) FROM transactions) AS AverageTransactionAmount,
  (SELECT AVG(likelihood) FROM predictions) AS AverageLikelihood;

SELECT *
FROM shopping_frequencies
WHERE frequency_name = 'Once or twice a month';

SELECT cohorts.cohort_name, predictions.future_trend
FROM cohorts
INNER JOIN predictions ON cohorts.cohort_id = predictions.cohort_id;

SELECT COUNT(channel_id) 
FROM shopping_channels 
WHERE channel_type = 'E-commerce';

SELECT *
FROM shopping_channels
WHERE channel_popularity = (
    SELECT MAX(channel_popularity)
    FROM shopping_channels
);
